age.total <- age.total %>% 
  rename(age.category = age,
  count.population = count,
  count.sample = n,
  percentage.population = percentage.x,
  percentage.sample = percentage.y)

age.total$age.category <- factor(age.total$age.category, levels = c(
"younger than 25",
"25-29",           "30-34",           "35-39",          
"40-44",           "45-49",           "50-54",
